'''伊恩·拉塞尔·麥克伊旺'''，[[CBE|CBE]]，[[皇家文藝學會|FRSA]]，[[皇家文學學會|FRSL]]（{{lang-en|'''Ian Russell McEwan'''}}，{{bd|1948年|6月21日|||M}}），[[英國|英國]][[小說家|小說家]]、[[作家|作家]]，其第一本短篇小说集《最初的爱情，最后的仪式》即获得1975年[[毛姆文學奖|毛姆文學奖]]，其《[[阿姆斯特丹_(小說)|阿姆斯特丹]]》獲得[[布克獎|布克獎]]肯定。

== 生平 ==
===早期===
伊恩·麥克伊旺於1948年6月21日出生[[罕布夏郡|罕布夏郡]][[奧爾德肖特|奧爾德肖特]]，雙親是大衛·麥克尤恩和莉蓮<ref name=filmr/>。他的父親是[[蘇格蘭|蘇格蘭]]工人，內容主要與[[軍隊|軍隊]]合作<ref>{{cite news|last=Cooke|first=Rachel|title=Ian McEwan: 'I had the time of my life'|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2012/aug/19/ian-mcewan-sweet-tooth-interview|newspaper=The Guardian|date=19 August 2012|accessdate=2013-09-17|archive-date=2013-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130212044053/http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2012/aug/19/ian-mcewan-sweet-tooth-interview|dead-url=no}}</ref>。伊恩·麥克伊旺在[[東亞|東亞]]地區（包括[[新加坡|新加坡]]）、[[德國|德國]]和[[北非|北非]]（包括[[利比亞|利比亞]]）度過了他的童年時代。他12歲的時候，全家返回英國。他曾就讀[[薩塞克斯大學|薩塞克斯大學]]，1970年獲得[[英語|英語]][[文學|文學]]學位。伊恩·麥克伊旺也曾在[[東英吉利大學|東英吉利大學]]學習，是[[馬爾科姆·布拉德伯里|馬爾科姆·布拉德伯里]]和[[安格斯·威爾遜|安格斯·威爾遜]]的學生，曾接受[[創意寫作課程|創意寫作課程]]。

===作家===
伊恩·麥克伊旺第一次發表的作品是短篇小說《最初的愛情，最後的儀式》（1975年），於1976年榮獲[[毛姆文學獎|毛姆文學獎]]<ref>''Ian McEwan: Writers and Their Work'' by Kiernan Ryan publ 1994</ref>。他的第二部短篇小說集《[[床笫之间|床笫之间]]》於1978年出版，《[[水泥花园|水泥花园]]》（1978年）與《[[只爱陌生人_(小說)|只爱陌生人]]》（1981年）是他最早的兩部小說，都被改編成[[電影|電影]]。這些作品的內容使他被暱稱為「死亡伊恩」<ref name="Independent">{{cite news | last = Walsh | first = John | title = Ian McEwan: Here's the twist | work = The Independent | date = 27 January 2007 | url = http://news.independent.co.uk/people/profiles/article2169220.ece | accessdate = 2007-03-22 | location = London | archive-date = 2007-03-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070329141454/http://news.independent.co.uk/people/profiles/article2169220.ece | dead-url = no }}</ref>。《[[时间中的孩子|时间中的孩子]]》是1987年[[惠特布雷德小說獎|惠特布雷德小說獎]]得主，《[[无辜者_(小說)|无辜者]]》與《[[黑犬_(小說)|黑犬]]》 是麥克伊旺之後的作品。麥克伊旺還寫了兩部兒童文學，分別是《玫瑰布蘭奇》（1985年）與《[[梦想家彼得|梦想家彼得]]》（1994年）。

伊恩·麥克伊旺於1997年完成的小說《[[愛無可忍|愛無可忍]]》深受評論家喜愛，雖然沒有入圍布克獎<ref>{{cite news | last = Knorr | first = Katherine | title = Enduring Love | work = International Herald Tribune | date = 9 October 1997 | url = http://www.iht.com/articles/1997/10/09/bookjeu.t.php | accessdate = 2007-03-22 | archive-date = 2008-03-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080330020341/http://www.iht.com/articles/1997/10/09/bookjeu.t.php | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Ian McEwan's Family Values | work=Boston Review | url=http://bostonreview.net/BR31.1/boylan.html | accessdate=2007-03-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061002002553/http://www.bostonreview.net/BR31.1/boylan.html | archive-date=2006-10-02 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。《[[愛無可忍|愛無可忍]]》後來在2004年被改編成電影。1998年，他以《阿姆斯特丹》贏得了布克獎<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.themanbookerprize.com/prize/archive/31 | publisher=Man Booker Prize | title=Prize archive: 1998 | accessdate=2010-07-07 | archive-date=2010-12-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203001414/http://www.themanbookerprize.com/prize/archive/31 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>[http://www.themanbookerprize.com/prize/archive/34 Man Booker Prize Website] {{Wayback|url=http://www.themanbookerprize.com/prize/archive/34 |date=20100103023232 }} 2010年4月13日參閱</ref>。他的下一部小說《贖罪》（2001年）獲得了相當多的正面評價，時代雜誌列為2002年最佳小說之一，它也入圍布克獎。《贖罪》在2007年改編成電影，導演是[[喬·懷特|喬·懷特]]，[[凱拉·奈特莉|凱拉·奈特莉]]和[[詹姆斯·麥卡沃伊|詹姆斯·麥卡沃伊]]主演。《[[星期六_(小說)|星期六]]》贏得了2005年[[詹姆斯·泰特·布莱克纪念奖|詹姆斯·泰特·布莱克纪念奖]]，《在切瑟爾海灘上》（2007年）也入圍2007年布克獎。伊恩·麥克伊旺也寫了一些劇本，舞台劇，兒童小說。

《追日》於2010年3月出版，伊恩·麥克伊旺在2008年6月曾透露這本小說的進度<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ianmcewan.com/bib/books/solar.html |title=Solar |publisher=Ian Mcewan's Website |accessdate=2011-08-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825073237/http://www.ianmcewan.com/bib/books/solar.html |archivedate=2011-08-25 }}</ref>。《追日》內容包括一位[[科學家|科學家]]，他希望拯救受到氣候變化威脅的[[地球|地球]]<ref name="guardian.co.uk">{{cite news | url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2008/jun/02/hayfestival2008.hayfestival | work=The Guardian | location=London | title=McEwan sees funny side of climate change in novel reading | date=2008-06-02 | accessdate=2010-04-02 | first=Judith | last=Soal | archive-date=2010-05-31 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100531081927/http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2008/jun/02/hayfestival2008.hayfestival | dead-url=no }}</ref>。伊恩·麥克伊旺的第十二部小說《甜食》是1970年代的歷史小說<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/authorinterviews/8359326/Ian-McEwan-interview.html# | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | first=Nigel | last=Farndale | title=Ian McEwan interview | date=2011-03-07 | accessdate=2013-09-17 | archive-date=2019-10-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029101204/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/authorinterviews/8359326/Ian-McEwan-interview.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，在2012年8月下旬出版<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ianmcewan.com/bib/books/sweettooth.html |title=Sweet Tooth |accessdate=2013-09-17 |archive-date=2012-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120503084444/http://www.ianmcewan.com/bib/books/sweettooth.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。根據2012年11月《[[華爾街日報|華爾街日報]]》的消息，《甜食》的電影版權已經出售。麥克伊旺的下一部小說與法院[[法官|法官]]有關<ref>{{cite news|last=Chai|first=Barbara|title=Working Title Secures Film Rights to Ian McEwan’s New Novel, ‘Sweet Tooth’|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2012/10/27/working-title-options-ian-mcewans-new-novel-sweet-tooth/|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|date=2012-10-27|accessdate=2013-09-17|archive-date=2019-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222160921/https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2012/10/27/working-title-options-ian-mcewans-new-novel-sweet-tooth/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Stock|first=Jon|title=Ian McEwan: John le Carré deserves Booker|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/10033653/Ian-McEwan-John-le-Carre-deserves-Booker.html|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=2013-05-03|accessdate=2013-09-17|archive-date=2020-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214023743/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/10033653/Ian-McEwan-John-le-Carre-deserves-Booker.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2006年，麥克伊旺被指控剽竊，從一本1977年出版的[[回憶錄|回憶錄]]中擷取文章當作《贖罪》（2001年）中的一段內容。麥克伊旺後來承認使用這本書作為作品的來源，但是否認抄襲的指控<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/28/books/28aton.html?pagewanted=1&_r=1 | work=The New York Times | first=Alan | last=Cowell | title=Eyebrows Are Raised Over Passages in a Best Seller by Ian McEwan | date=2006-11-28 | accessdate=2013-09-17 | archive-date=2019-10-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191018215722/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/28/books/28aton.html?pagewanted=1&_r=1 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Mail1">{{cite news | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-418598/Ian-McEwan-accused-stealing-ideas-romance-novelist.html | work=The Daily Mail | location=London | title=Ian McEwan accused of stealing ideas from romance novelist | author=Julia Langdon | date=25 November 2006 | accessdate=2010-07-07 | archive-date=2019-03-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190324062513/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-418598/Ian-McEwan-accused-stealing-ideas-romance-novelist.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/28/books/28aton.html?ex=1322370000&en=998492a2933f783c&ei=5090&partner=rssuserland&emc=rss | work=The New York Times | title=Eyebrows Are Raised Over Passages in a Best Seller by Ian McEwan | author=Alan Cowell | date=28 November 2006 | accessdate=2010-07-07 | archive-date=2018-08-31 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831002437/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/28/books/28aton.html?ex=1322370000&en=998492a2933f783c&ei=5090&partner=rssuserland&emc=rss | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Guardian">{{cite news | title=An inspiration, yes. Did I copy from another author? No | work=The Guardian | location=London | url=http://books.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,,1957845,00.html | author=Ian McEwan | accessdate=27 November 2006 | date=2006-11-27 | archive-date=2008-10-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081010224656/http://books.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,,1957845,00.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=McEwan hits back at call for atonement | work=The Times | location=London | url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,2-2473382,00.html | accessdate=27 November 2006 | date=2006-11-27 | first=Ben | last=Hoyle | archive-date=2008-12-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081202070316/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,2-2473382,00.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=McEwan accused of copying writers memoirs | work=PR inside | url=http://www.pr-inside.com/mcewan-accused-of-copying-writer-s-memoirs-r27254.htm | accessdate=2006-11-27 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070326135840/http://www.pr-inside.com/mcewan-accused-of-copying-writer-s-memoirs-r27254.htm | archivedate=2007-03-26 }}</ref>。有一些作家也為他辯護，包括[[約翰·厄普代克|約翰·厄普代克]]、[[馬丁·艾米斯|馬丁·艾米斯]]、[[瑪格麗特·阿特伍德|瑪格麗特·阿特伍德]]、[[托馬斯·肯尼利|托馬斯·肯尼利]]、[[石黑一雄|石黑一雄]]，[[扎迪·史密斯|扎迪·史密斯]]、[[托馬斯·品欽|托馬斯·品欽]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/2006/12/06/nwriter06.xml | work=The Daily Telegraph | location=London | title=Recluse speaks out to defend McEwan | first=Nigel | last=Reynolds | date=6 December 2006 | accessdate=2010-04-25 | archive-date=2008-04-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080420232306/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=%2Fnews%2F2006%2F12%2F06%2Fnwriter06.xml | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://books.guardian.co.uk/news/articles/0,,1965130,00.html | work=The Guardian | location=London | title=Pynchon backs McEwan in 'copying' row | date=6 December 2006 | accessdate=2010-04-25 | first=Dan | last=Bell | archive-date=2007-12-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071229090400/http://books.guardian.co.uk/news/articles/0,,1965130,00.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==榮譽==
伊恩·麥克伊旺已入圍布克獎六次，並贏得1998年布克獎。《只爱陌生人》（1981年）、《黑犬》（1992年）、《贖罪》（2001年）、《星期六》（2005年）、《在切瑟爾海灘上》（2007年）都有入圍布克獎，伊恩·麥克伊旺還在2005年和2007年獲得[[布克國際獎|布克國際獎]]的提名<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.themanbookerprize.com/prize/authors/38 |title=Man Booker |publisher=Themanbookerprize.com |accessdate=2011-08-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819095354/http://www.themanbookerprize.com/prize/authors/38 |archivedate=2011-08-19 }}</ref>。

伊恩·麥克伊旺是[[皇家文學學會|皇家文學學會]]資深會員、[[皇家文艺學會|皇家文艺學會]]會員、[[美國藝術與科學學院|美國藝術與科學學院]]院士。1999年，他於[[漢堡|漢堡]]被授予[[阿爾弗雷德·特普費爾基金會|阿爾弗雷德·特普費爾基金會]]設立的[[莎士比亞獎|莎士比亞獎]]。他亦是一位傑出的[[英國人文主義協會|英國人文主義協會]]的支持者。他在2000年被授予了[[大英帝國勳章|大英帝國勳章]]<ref name="ContemporaryWriters">{{cite web | title = Ian McEwan | work = Contemporary Writers | publisher = British Council | url = http://www.contemporarywriters.com/authors/?p=auth70 | accessdate = 2006-06-03 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060617183752/http://www.contemporarywriters.com/authors/?p=auth70 | archivedate = 2006-06-17 }}</ref>。2005年，他是[[迪金森學院|迪金森學院]]的哈羅德和埃塞爾·史特福訪問學者和作家獎第一個得主。2008年，伊恩·麥克伊旺被[[倫敦大學學院|倫敦大學學院]]授予榮譽[[文學博士|文學博士]]學位。2008年，《[[泰晤士報|泰晤士報]]》將伊恩·麥克伊旺列入「1945年以來最偉大的50位英國作家」名單<ref>{{cite news | date=5 January 2008 | url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/books/article3127837.ece | title=The 50 greatest British writers since 1945 | work=The Times | accessdate=1 February 2010 | location=London | first1=Patrick | last1=Hosking | first2=David | last2=Wighton | archive-date=2011-04-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110425050801/http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/books/article3127837.ece | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[薩塞克斯大學|薩塞克斯大學]]在2012年授予麥克伊旺50週年金獎，以表彰他對文學的貢獻<ref>[http://www.sussex.ac.uk/newsandevents/?id=14527] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sussex.ac.uk/newsandevents/?id=14527 |date=20170214094231 }} "Sussex awards gold medals to its world-leading alumni and past academics"</ref>。麥克伊旺在2010年獲得[[黑爾梅里希傑出作家獎|黑爾梅里希傑出作家獎]]，該獎由[[塔爾薩圖書館信託基金|塔爾薩圖書館信託基金]]設立。2011年2月20日，他被授予[[耶路撒冷獎|耶路撒冷獎]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jerusalembookfair.com/the_jerusalem_prize.html |title=the jerusalem prize |publisher=Jerusalem Book Fair |accessdate=2011-02-13 |archive-date=2012-05-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120520205606/http://www.jerusalembookfair.com/the_jerusalem_prize.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>[http://www.jewishjournal.com/books/article/mcewan_defends_decision_to_accept_jerusalem_prize_20110126 "McEwan defends decision to accept Jerusalem Prize."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jewishjournal.com/books/article/mcewan_defends_decision_to_accept_jerusalem_prize_20110126 |date=20130929071934 }} ''Jewish Journal''. 26 January 2011. 26 January 2011.</ref>。儘管出現爭議，並面臨反對[[以色列|以色列]]的壓力，他最終還是接受該獎項<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2011/jan/19/ian-mcewan-accept-jerusalem-prize | location=London | work=The Guardian | first=Stephen | last=Bates | title=Ian McEwan says he will accept Jerusalem prize | date=2011-01-19 | accessdate=2013-09-17 | archive-date=2011-01-28 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110128171058/http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2011/jan/19/ian-mcewan-accept-jerusalem-prize | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jan/27/mcewan-should-turn-down-prize | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=Ian McEwan should turn down the prize | date=2011-01-27 | accessdate=2013-09-17 | archive-date=2012-02-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120225151849/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jan/27/mcewan-should-turn-down-prize | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

